.TH "t3_sge_init_rspcntxt" 9 "t3_sge_init_rspcntxt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t3_sge_init_rspcntxt \- initialize an SGE response queue context
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t3_sge_init_rspcntxt
.BI "(struct adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "unsigned int id "  ","
.BI "int irq_vec_idx "  ","
.BI "u64 base_addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ","
.BI "unsigned int fl_thres "  ","
.BI "int gen "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cidx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
the adapter to configure
.IP "id" 12
the context id
.IP "irq_vec_idx" 12
MSI-X interrupt vector index, 0 if no MSI-X, -1 if no IRQ
.IP "base_addr" 12
base address of queue
.IP "size" 12
number of queue entries
.IP "fl_thres" 12
threshold for selecting the normal or jumbo free list
.IP "gen" 12
initial generation value for the context
.IP "cidx" 12
consumer pointer

Initialize an SGE response queue context and make it ready for use.
The caller is responsible for ensuring only one context operation
occurs at a time.
